Task.Name: Microsoft Windows SharePoint Services Deployment
Task.Notes:
This template is designed to help you identify and execute the tasks necessary to successfully deploy Windows SharePoint Services and migrate from Microsoftâ€™s SharePoint Team Services. Use resources available from http://www.microsoft.com/SharePoint to assist with the details of this effort. In addition, you can leverage resources available in other templates including the Microsoft Office SharePoint Portal Server "v2.0" Deployment template, the Microsoft Windows 2003 Server deployment template, and the Microsoft Office System Deployment template.
See Help to learn more about each section of this template.

Task.Name: Identify team collaboration vision concerns (multinational, etc.)

Determine Windows SharePoint Services components to install to meet goals
Determine number of users in each role
Determine Required Server Capacity from Role Analysis
Determine architecture for servers (e.g. single box or Web farm, single database server or clustering, etc.)
Identify interoperability issues with applications (SharePoint technologies versions, Microsoft Office System program versions, suites, etc.)
Identify interoperability issues with the organization's partners (SharePoint technologies versions, Microsoft Office System program versions, suites, etc.)
Identify interoperability issues with third-party packages
Identify Migration Strategies (If Currently Using SharePoint Team Services)
Develop document migration strategy for SharePoint Team Services
Identify SharePoint Team Services subwebs for proactive document migration (mass conversion)
Identify SharePoint Team Services subwebs for "as-used" migration (requires SharePoint Team Services remains on separate servers)
Identify SharePoint Team Services subwebs not being migrated
Diagram and document external user connections
Configure a VPN solution as needed
Plan upgrade to Windows Server 2003 as required (you may want to use the Windows 2003 Server Deployment template to help)
Identify Web servers for Windows SharePoint Services
Identify database servers for Windows SharePoint Services
Identify users of Microsoft Windows NT, Microsoft Windows 2000, Microsoft Windows XP
Document work-arounds and procedures for users of older versions of Web browsers
Determine browser upgrade strategy as needed

Determine Microsoft Office upgrade strategy as needed (if performing a Microsoft Office System upgrade refer to the Microsoft Office System Deployment template for more information)

Determine message "from account" and configure mailbox appropriately
Plan integration with Microsoft SharePoint Portal Server "v2.0" as desired (see Microsoft SharePoint Portal Server "v2.0" Deployment template for more information)
Evaluate the Active Directory account configuration tool for management of users and permissions
Identify plans for providing localized content
Identify and train a systems administrator

Configure Microsoft SharePoint Portal Server "v2.0" integration as desired (See Microsoft SharePoint Portal Server "v2.0" Deployment template for more information)
Upgrade client operating systems as needed
Upgrade client Microsoft Office System versions as desired
Perform Migration from SharePoint Team Services
Select full backup and restore approach
